their studies at Rutgers, and in his unprecedented role in early Japanese-American relations. This fascinating story uncovers a little-known link between Rutgers University and Japan, and it is the only book to conclude that Rutgers made a greater contribution to the development of modern education in the early Meiji Era than any other non-Japanese college or university in the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aCollege teacherszNew JerseyvBiography. 0aEducation and statezJapanxHistoryy19th century. 0aEducationzJapanxHistoryy19th century. 0aEducatorszJapanvBiography. 0aPublic schoolszJapanxHistoryy19th century. 0aRutgers CollegexEmployeesvBiography. 7aEDUCATION / General.2bisacsh  aJapan, Rutgers, Rutgers University, David Murray, education, Ministry of Education, Gakusei, Code of Education, samurai, Japanese American.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGz978311061013008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2019z9783110606485oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z97831106660830 cprintz978081359497240uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/9780813595016?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813595016423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780813595016/original  a978-3-11-061013-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-066608-3  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Packag